<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Dissappointed After carefully combing through guidebooks and TripAdvisor, I chose La Casona as our home during our introduction to Mexico City. We stayed 4 nights and ultimately left feeling dissappointed with our wallets lighter than we would have liked. We booked online in order to receive a cheaper rate which included breakfast - the rooms at La Casona do not include breakfast unless you pay for it. Our room was on the ground floor and has several problems with it. Firstly, the decor was nothing like the pictures on their website on in their brochure; our beadspread and curtains resembled somethig out of a cheap motel more than the fluffy florals in their pictures. Secondly, the noise from the street was extremely noisy every morning, with cars honking for 2 hours straight. The room was also quite dark. Breakfast was pleasant as were the staff, but ultimately I felt as if we did not receive value for our money. I had thought that some of the other disgruntled reviewers were perhaps grumpy people, but I left agreeing with their criticisms. For example, we were given one robe to use with our room, which was nice. After 3 days we left it on the floor with the towels only to find it dirty and back on the hook when we returned that day. Also, there are hidden charges added to the bill such as daily tips (we had already been tipping the staff on a daily basis) and fees for their taxi service (which, to be fair, is posted in their lobby and we didn't mind paying as it was safe and reliable). Although a nice hotel in a pleasant neighbourhood, there is much better value to be had in Mexico City. 
